pf.analytics
Interface Line

All Known Subinterfaces:
GridLine
All Known Implementing Classes:
GridLineImpl, LineImpl
public interface Line

This represents a line defined by two Points.

Most methods suppose this line is infinitely long, but this can be implementation specific. Some methods are similar to those in Line2D

Because of integer based interface Point some methods can have an interesting behavior: Point returned by getPoint may not lie ( contains==false) on this line.

Author:
Adam Juraszek

extend

Line extend(float factor)
Makes the line factor-times longer to both ends.

factor=0: returned line is the same
factor=1: returned line is three times longer
factor: returned line is (factor*2+1) times longer

Parameters:
factor - how much bigger is the new line
Returns:
longer line

Point getPoint(float factor)
